{
  "text": "By investigating the annual reports for 2001 of 100 French firms belonging to the SBF 120 stock index, Chavent et al. [CITATION_1] found that the disclosure pattern is associated with provision intensity, size, leverage, and market expectation. Companies with the highest score for disclosures have the greatest provision intensity, firm size, leverage, and market expectation.",
  "citation_candidates": [
